description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Acute Surgical Receiving Unit (ASU) at Wythenshawe Hospital of Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust are seeking experienced or newly qualified Registered Nurses to join our team. This an exciting time to be joining our fantastic team as we are now receiving emergency ambulatory care patients in our Surgical Ambulatory Care Receiving Unit (SACRU) as well as acutely unwell surgical patients on ASU.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking proactive, forward thinking Nurses who have patient care and experience at their heart. You will possess adept communication skills, be motivated and eager to embrace variety in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nursing roles at The Manchester University Hospital Foundation Trust (MFT) are about having access to fantastic learning facilities and developmental opportunities. You will have access to the MFT Academy and LEAD Training Programmes, coaching, and department specific training and development opportunities. Our commitment is further reinforced by our robust Trust Nurse Revalidation Programme – offering an e-portfolio and dedicated individual support. We can offer training, flexibility, friendliness and a caring environment in which to work and provide a number of benefits, which you will find on the attached document entitled &quot;Staff Benefits.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameChristopher LewisJob titleWard ManagerEmail addresschristopher.lewis@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 291 6698Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information or to arrange an informal visit, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris Lewis / Emma Cooke / Geena Roy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Managers - ASU&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0161 291 6698 / 6499&lt;/p&gt;
